summary:
• FY2025 Results Announcement Date: 21 August 2025 (with live webcast at 10.30am NZST).
  • Annual Report Publication Date: 30 September 2025.
  • Annual Meeting Date: 13 November 2025 (hybrid, Ashburton, NZ).

No material financial or operational information disclosed.

Quarterly Report Summary (Hydrology & Generation Update):

  • FY25 Hydro Generation: 3,410 GWh (17% below PCP), 4th lowest Waikato scheme output since 1980.
  • FY26 Forward Outlook: Mean hydro generation forecast raised to 4,140 GWh/year (+62 GWh) due to:
  • Karāpiro Hydro Rehab: Third unit completion (Sep-25), adding 16.5MW capacity (32 GWh/year avg. uplift).
  • Digital River AI: Improved efficiency, contributing to FY25 record hydro performance.
  • Market Prices: FY26–27 Auckland forward prices at $179/MWh (vs. FY25 spot avg. $216/MWh).
  • Storage Recovery: Q4 inflows lifted Waikato catchment to 79th percentile, improving FY26 storage levels.

Omitted: Market share stats, background details on non-material assets.

Material Information Summary

Index Change Announcement

  • Infratil Limited (IFT) will be added to the S&P/ASX 200 Index, effective open of trading on 23 July 2025.
  • Spartan Resources Limited (SPR) will be removed (due to acquisition by Ramelius Resources Limited (RMS)), same effective date (23 July 2025).

No other material information identified.

Here is the concise extraction of material information from Meridian Energy's June 2025 monthly operating report:

Key Highlights (June 2025)

  • Hydro Storage
  • National hydro storage increased to 104% of historical average (from 94%).
  • South Island storage at 95%, North Island at 150% of average.
  • Inflows
  • Total inflows: 111% of historical average.
  • Waiau catchment inflows: 113% of average.
  • Electricity Demand & Prices
  • National demand: +1.4% YoY.
  • NZ Aluminium Smelter (NZAS) avg. load: 530MW.
  • Average generation price: $121/MWh (down 54.2% YoY).
  • Retail Sales
  • Volumes: +7.9% YoY (Residential +12.7%, Large Business +15.2%).
  • Customer connections: +9.6% YoY.

Quarterly (Q4 2025) Highlights

  • Generation & Pricing
  • Generation volume: -8.8% YoY, avg. price -18.6% YoY.
  • Electricity futures prices declined across winter quarters.
  • Retail Performance
  • Sales volumes: +2.9% YoY, avg. price +5.2% YoY.
  • NZAS Update
  • Demand response agreement to end by 11 August 2025.

Operational Costs & Capex

  • Operating costs: -0.2% YoY.
  • Capex: -16.5% YoY.

No material capital raising or trading halt information identified.

Note: Excludes routine operational details and non-material commentary.
